@raverboy112 - SolidSoldier and subsequently Jedijoe are both right.   

Pro something means it cannot be targeted by spells or abilities of the appropriate protection, blocked (in most cases at least, except such cases when a creature is put into play already blocking, such as one from the new schemes in archenemy.) and all **damage** dealt to it would be prevented with exception of other rare cases such as me attacking with an [Excruciator](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Excruciator) and you block it with Akroma, it would kill the Akroma even though she has pro red. Mass removal though, does not deal damage, nor does it target, thus getting around protection and killing Akroma, if in fact the [Reiver Demon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reiver Demon) was cast from a player's hand. xD  

Yay bandwagons! also, it's spelled geniuses\*\*
